the ml/i macro processor.wa general purpose macro processor called ml/iis described.  ml/i has been implemented on the pdp- and i.c.t. atlas  computers and is intended as atool to allow users to extend any existing programming language by incorporating new statements and othersyntactic forms of their own choosing and in their own notation.  this allows a complete user-orientedlanguage to be built up with relative ease.cacm october, brown, p. j.ca jb february ,   : pm